gs of each mimetic form. All examples appear in Japanese orthography, in romanization, and in English translation. Concise information is provided concerning the varieties of syntactic usage appropriate for each mimetic. An extensive English index facilitates comparison of English and Japanese vocabulary.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aJapanese languagevDictionariesxEnglish. 0aJapanese languagexMimetic wordsvDictionaries. 4aIronie. 4aJapanisch. 4aWortfeld. 4aWörterbuch. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Reference.2bisacsh1 aEmerson, Leslie J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchourup, Lawrence, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTamori, Ikuhiro, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Library Information Science 1990 - 1999z9783110636222oZDB-23-GLI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION: BEST OF LINGUISTICSz9783110233940oZDB-23-DGO0 cprintz978311012810940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311080904640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110809046423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110809046/original  a978-3-11-064968-0  Asian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Package  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGO  aZDB-23-GLIc1990d1999